* Iron Raptor crept a little closer as she saw Prowl move, but the face that 
it was only her arms worried her.
And with a simple scan, she detected why.
Something was wrong with his main processor, something which seems as if it 
had been ripped from it.

Iron Raptor came up beside Prowl and looked down at his back, gently moving 
the broken wing out of the way.
She looked at the back of his neck but there was no telling from the outside 
just what was wrong.
Moving him could damage even more, but she had the faintest idea of just 
what to do.
With much doubt Iron Raptor dug in a long claw into the back of his neck, 
relying on senses and touch to see just what had disconected.
And she was sure that if Prowl could scream now, he would.*
